==English==

===Noun===
'''C-47'''
# ''(filmmaking jargon)'' A standard wooden [[clothespin]], used to hold gels to the [[barn doors]] of cinema lights.

There are two stories as to how this name came about. 

One is that producers would never pay for clothespins, so the numerical code was devised. 

The other is that C 47 was the original cataloge number of clothespins, and it just became the name.

===Alternative spellings===
*C47
